My Meme

Had a little joke with my mother that backfired when she saw my 2% total grade, because that was all that was possible at the time. 

library(magick)
#Load all the image links
explaining <- image_read("https://www.looper.com/img/gallery/the-best-cold-opens-on-brooklyn-nine-nine-ranked/intro-1605551636.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(500)

disappointed <- image_read("https://64.media.tumblr.com/a10e3acfd4472a05f15baec1f021a253/tumblr_n4azc8os3r1sl3jhqo1_1280.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(500)

happy <- image_read("https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/a6c0ec5ffca421788f1b66419e7d7b5bad6b9a18/0_128_3000_1800/master/3000.jpg?width=620&quality=85&dpr=1&s=none") %>%
  image_scale(500)
#Make the text boxes
the_truth <- image_blank(width = 500, 
                         height = 281, 
                         color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Explaining to my parents\n I'm doing good in Stats220",
                 color = "#FFFFFF",
                 size = 30,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")

the_implication <- image_blank(width = 500, 
                               height = 281, 
                               color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Them not believing me because they saw a D-",
                 color = "#FFFFFF",
                 size = 25,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")

the_conclusion <- image_blank(width = 500, 
                              height = 300, 
                              color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Turning on \n Calculate based on Graded Assignments\nAnd seeing the A+",
                 color = "#FFFFFF",
                 size = 28,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")
#Link the images with the text
first_row <- c(explaining, the_truth) %>%
  image_append()

second_row <- c(disappointed, the_implication) %>%
  image_append()

third_row <- c(happy, the_conclusion) %>%
  image_append()
#Stack the 3 rows
meme <- c(first_row, second_row, third_row) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE)
#Save image as my_meme.png
image_write(meme, "my_meme.png")
